    {
      "id": "2b830a56-0007-4752-8602-204b46855c8a",
      "url": "/doc/logging-convention-r7LT2oFrCx",
      "urlId": "r7LT2oFrCx",
      "title": "Logging Convention",
      "text": "# Logging Convention\n\n## Status\n\nActive — applies to all apps and services under hephaestustest/\\*.\n\n## Rule\n\nAll diagnostic output MUST go through the platform structured logger (`os.Logger` on Apple platforms, SLF4J on the JVM). Bare `print(...)` / `println` / `NSLog` statements are FORBIDDEN in production code. Every log line must carry a subsystem and category so it can be filtered in Console/observability tooling.\n\n## Rationale\n\nBare print statements bypass log levels, cannot be filtered or redacted, leak into release builds, and are invisible to our observability pipeline. A single structured logging facade keeps diagnostics consistent and privacy-safe.\n\n## Enforcement\n\nCode review MUST reject any new `print(...)` call in production source. Debug scaffolding must be removed before merge.",
      "icon": null,
      "color": null,
      "tasks": {
        "completed": 0,
        "total": 0
      },
