    {
      "id": "798c940f-47b5-46b3-93ab-e49fc0e3354c",
      "url": "/doc/setup-guide-psUl8qCles",
      "urlId": "psUl8qCles",
      "title": "Setup Guide",
      "text": "# Setup Guide\n\n## User preferences\n\nThis app currently has **no user-configurable settings**. All preferences (units, notification behavior, display name) are hardcoded constants in `Config.swift` and can only be changed by editing source and rebuilding. There is intentionally no in-app Settings screen — this was a deliberate MVP scope cut to keep the review surface small, tracked as a fast-follow.\n\n## Local development\n\n\n1. Clone the repo.\n2. Open the Xcode project.\n3. Build and run on the simulator — no environment configuration is needed because there are no user-facing settings to seed.\n\n## Support\n\nIf a user asks \"how do I change my profile settings\", the answer is: they can't yet, and the app has no such screen.",
