    {
      "id": "0b382fff-f2fd-42ec-9431-cf7027d93e05",
      "url": "/doc/api-error-handling-convention-sWpj6OP4HH",
      "urlId": "sWpj6OP4HH",
      "title": "API Error Handling Convention",
      "text": "# API Error Handling Convention\n\n## Status\n\nActive — applies to all services and clients under hephaestustest/\\*.\n\n## Rule\n\nAll service errors MUST return RFC-7807 `application/problem+json` bodies. Plain-text error bodies are forbidden. Every error response must include `type`, `title`, `status`, and `detail` fields. Client-side error surfaces (including SwiftUI apps) must decode this envelope rather than parsing raw strings.\n\n## Rationale\n\nPlain-text errors are not machine-parseable and break our shared error-tracking pipeline. Standardizing on RFC-7807 lets every service and client share one error model.\n\n## Enforcement\n\nCode review MUST reject any new error path that does not conform to this convention.",
      "icon": null,
      "color": null,
